  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "ブル・ボルター、ヨーマ一族の主がチャイナランドに侵入し、皇帝を捕らえました。彼は王国全体にテレビ放送を送り、自らを支配者と宣言します。ジャックとリュウはチャイナランドの忍者マスターで、エピン山で師匠のもとで修行しています。皇帝の捕獲のニュースを聞いた彼らは、ブル・ボルターと彼のヨーマ一族を倒すために旅立ちます。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Little Ninja Brothers, known in Japan as Super Chinese 2, is a 1989 video game developed and published by Culture Brain for the Nintendo Entertainment System in 1989 in Japan, 1990 in the United States, and 1991 in Europe. It is the second game in the Super Chinese series. The plot follows two young ninjas, Jack and Ryu, attempting to find out the mysterious reason for the invasion of Chinaland by Blu Boltar. It was the second game in the series, preceded by Kung-Fu Heroes, and followed up by a sequel Super Ninja Boy, released on the Super NES. There were also two Ninja Boy spin-off games released for the Game Boy in both regions. A manga adaption of the game was serialized in early issues of video game magazine GamePro.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
